  }
  m_iOrder 5
 }
 G6_Notes {
  coords 0 0 0
  m_sTitle "Mission Notes"
  m_sTextData "- Setup Timer: 5 minutes (affects NVA helicopter and US)"\
  "- US defeat end condition is fairly lenient, it's the COs job to call it when deemed appropriate."\
  "- It is against mission maker intent that the NVA maneuvers around the US advance and attacks from the rear, as there would be follow and support forces."\
  "- There are capture messages however they can only be seen by US players"\
  "- Surviving crew of destroyed US vehicles can mount up in the Bradleys and play infantry, or ascend to specpen"
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 6
 }
 N1_Situation {
  coords 0 0 0
  m_sTitle "I. SITUATION"
  m_sTextData "<b>a. Enemy Forces</b>"\
  ""\
  "US Abrams tanks and Bradley IFVs were observed south of Koskelankyla."\
  "It is likely they are preparing to counterattack north, attempting to regain territory currently occupied by a friendly motor rifle battalion."\
  ""\
  "Most likely, the armored-mechanized force will attempt to penetrate its defense, assaulting some positons while bypassing others, while additional forces will follow and support."\
  ""\
  ""\
  "<b>b. Friendly Forces</b>"\
  ""\
  "One friendly motorized rifle battalion supported by T-72As and equipped with SPW-70s, occupying the area after a recent advance."\
  "You (071 055) are part of an additonal T-72A company tasked with supporting the defense."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_NVA"
  }
  m_iOrder 1
 }
 N2_Mission {
  coords 0 0 0
  m_sTitle "II. MISSION"
  m_sTextData "The tank platoon will support the defense of the area between Pauhu and Ruhanpera with the goal of stopping or delaying the armored counterattack."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_NVA"
  }
  m_iOrder 2
 }
 N3_Execution {
  coords 0 0 0
  m_sTitle "III. EXECUTION"
  m_sTextData "<b>a. Commander's Intent</b>"\
  ""\
  "The intent of this operation is to retain control of some of the area, which is a prerequisite for further mechanized attacks along the railway line."\
  ""\
  "To achieve this, the tank platoon will support the defense of friendly forces in the area and delay the enemies advance."\
  ""\
  ""\
  "<b>b. Concept of the operation</b>"\
  ""\
  "It is likely that the initially advancing force will only assault some positions while bypassing others, while additional forces would follow and support, securing remaining areas."\
  ""\
  "Contact with follow and support forces MUST be avoided, therefor you should not attempt to maneuver around the intial advance and attack from the rear. If enemy forces are about to bypass you, fall back immediately."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_NVA"
  }
  m_iOrder 3
 }
 N4_Service {
  coords 0 0 0
  m_sTitle "IV. SERVICE SUPPORT"
  m_sTextData "<b>a. Service</b>"\
  ""\
  "None, both for tanks and helicopter"\
  ""\
  ""\
  "<b>b. Support</b>"\
  ""\
  "One Mi-24P, armed with 4 ATGMs, a fixed 30mm autocannon and 4 rocket pods (starts near 051 075)."\
  "It is not under command of the tank platoon and can attack without support being explicitly requested, but coordination is recommended."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_NVA"
  }
  m_iOrder 4
 }
